About Project:

Project Name: House Price Prediction System using Linear Regression in C++.
Author: Yogeshwar Prakash Chaudhari.
File Name: Final.cpp

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Project Description:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1) This project is a C++ based console application that predicts house prices using a Multiple Linear Regression model. 
  The system learns from historical housing data (area, number of bedrooms, bathrooms, age of the house, and location) and builds 
  a regression model to estimate property prices.

2) The program supports importing and exporting data in CSV format, training the model on historical data, and predicting prices 
   for new houses entered by the user. All predictions and data are saved for future reference.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Key Features:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1) Data Management
Load housing data from a CSV file.
Add new house records manually.
Store historical data persistently in historical_data.csv.

2) Linear Regression Training
Uses the Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) method to compute regression coefficients.

 Considers multiple factors:
    Area (sq. ft.)
    Bedrooms
    Bathrooms
    Age of the house
    Location score (numerical encoding of city/locality).

3) Prediction
Given new house details, the model predicts the price.
Predictions are saved in predictions.csv.
Outputs result in Indian Rupees.

4) User Interface
Console menu system for easy navigation.
Options: Load data, Add data, Display data, Train model, Predict prices, Exit.

5) Dynamic Memory Handling
Expands dataset dynamically when new houses exceed capacity.
Manages memory safely with constructors and destructors.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Technologies Used:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1) Programming Language: C++

2) Concepts Applied:
Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
Dynamic memory allocation
File handling (CSV read/write)
Multiple Linear Regression (OLS method)

3) Data Format: CSV

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Workflow:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1) Data Loading
Read past house records from CSV files.

2) Training Phase
Build regression model by calculating coefficients using matrix operations (XtX and XtY).

3) Prediction Phase
Take input for a new house.
Apply trained coefficients to predict price.

4) Output
Show predicted price on console.
Store prediction in predictions.csv.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Learning Outcomes:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Hands-on experience with Data Structures and Dynamic Arrays in C++.
Implementation of a Machine Learning concept (Linear Regression) from scratch without external libraries.
Practice in file handling and data persistence.
Understanding of how location, size, and features affect property prices.

This project demonstrates how machine learning concepts can be implemented in pure C++, bridging theoretical knowledge with practical, real-world applications.
